What is Rollups as a Service (RaaS) and Why is Demand Increasing?
Rollups as a Service (RaaS) is an emerging blockchain infrastructure solution that enables developers and enterprises to deploy Layer-2 rollup networks without managing the complex technical processes involved in blockchain scaling. These managed platforms abstract infrastructure deployment, validator management, security configurations, and network maintenance, allowing developers to focus on building decentralized applications instead of blockchain operations.

Unlike traditional blockchain deployment methods, RaaS platforms bundle transactions off-chain before submitting them to Layer-1 blockchains such as Ethereum, significantly increasing throughput while reducing transaction costs. Supporting both Optimistic Rollups and Zero-Knowledge (ZK) Rollups, modern RaaS platforms provide scalable infrastructure for high-performance Web3 applications across decentralized finance, gaming, NFTs, enterprise blockchain, and digital identity ecosystems.

